summary: Wow, Game of Thrones season 8 episode 3 “The Long Night” was really epic! I loved the battle and the girls did the best and...
caption:
Wow, Game of Thrones season 8 episode 3 “The Long Night” was really epic!

I loved the battle and the girls did the best and killed the worst ones! 

I can’t believe Arya killed the Night King, thought it’d be Jon, it looked like it would be but then she came out of nowhere and killed him so all the other White Walkers died. 

Although, I must say, I did think the battle against them would be the final battle of the show overall and maybe after someone had got the Throne and it would’ve last more than one episode. They were made out to be like the big bad of the show and I thought it’d be like a battle over the course of several episodes at the very end of the show and killing the Night King would maybe be the last thing we saw before the credits rolled of the last episode. I would’ve liked that, that would’ve been a good ending.

I can’t wait to see how it ends though, even if it’s not how I thought it’d be <3

Kit Harington and Nikolaj Coster-Waldau <3

summary:
Arya is so satisfying as a character.
She starts off as this wild child who can barely contain her emotions at times and evolves...
body:
Arya is so satisfying as a character.

She starts off as this wild child who can barely contain her emotions at times and evolves into this woman who is so closed lipped it unnerves people. Her eyes are always watching and taking things in and she looks as if she knows more than she tells. It looks like she’s wanting for the perfect minute to pounce.

The way she appears and disappears or that she’s almost always in control of the conversation. The unpredictability about her.

How she goes from the student to the teacher and leaves people stunned at the accuracy and precision of her fighting/combat.

And the moments she breaks her facade is so earned. Like her fight with brienne when she got excited into provoking brienne into really fighting or her first time with Gendry when she’s kissing her intimately.

And it’s not as if she’s always quiet or doesn’t have a personality. She’s witty, sarcastic, scathing, a smart ass, etc.

She still has her humanity.

Everything about her fucking character arc is earned!

Ugh…I love her so much. 😩😩😩

summary: Knowing very little about fan theories for GOT, I liked how 8x03 went down but would have added four things. 1. The NK stabbing...
body:
Knowing very little about fan theories for GOT, I liked how 8x03 went down but would have added four things.

1. The NK stabbing Bran before Arya gets to him.

2. Jon and the NK having it out on the battlefield, Jon losing and the NK doesn’t finish him off but leaves him to the zombies. 

3. The zombie generals should have participated in the battle instead of just being bros to the NK. Maybe Brienne and Jaime or Sandor could have killed one together.

4. Wanted to see Sansa kill a wight with Tyrion.

summary: If you listen and watch carefully, it could totally look like Jon actually saw Arya trying to get to the Godswood and since...
body:
Jon helped Arya (?)

If you listen and watch carefully, it could totally look like Jon actually saw Arya trying to get to the Godswood and since Viserion was watching the entrance, he could have gotten up to distract him and when it seemed like he was screaming nonsense he could have actually been yelling “GO!”

And my friends, if this is true, then it means my duo of siblings really somehow came together to end the long night and Jon helped Arya to get where she needed to be to kill the Night King AND I WILL LITERALLY FLING MYSELF INTO THE SUN BECAUSE THEY’D BE BOTH HEROES FOR THE DAWN.
